<br>
In general I had between 60 and 75 though.<br>
<br>
Its up to Farrn, but I never put a cap on them myself.  For starters its an experience type thing, and the more people who get to see things, the better.<br>
<br>
Yeah, yeah I know 98% of them were there for extra shots at an epic drop, but I gave em the benefit of the doubt.<br>
<br>
And yeah, it tended to lag a lot.  But thats the price of a KCoG raid really.  You want small, tight, easy to run plane raids, then take your guild up and do it solo.  I know WM typically does it with about 12-18 people.  Takes us about 5 or so hours to totally clear the place.  And we're far from uber.  Most of us arent even in full Velious gear.<br>
<br>
On a more practical level, when you start turning people away, you end up turning away people who may not come back the next time when you need them because you are short.  Things have changed for KCoG over the last 3 years.  But I do know when we first started doing these, occasionally people would be turned away.  Since some raids we'd have 70+ people.  Then the next raid we'd have 25 or so people show up with others saying, Gosh...we didnt think we'd be needed.<br>
<br>
Still, that was several years ago back when KCoG had trouble breaking into the planes.  Times have changed a lot, so it might not be as much of a problem anymore.<br>
<br>
There are often caps on the dragon raids because people going LD on the charge or even during buffing is bad.  But its generally less of a problem on the plane raids.<br>
<br>
Personally though, I never had much problem with people complaining.  Most were just happy to be there.  And any complaints were generally dealt with the same way.  I'd just remove the healers from that group.  Its remarkable how much more compliant a group gets when they realize they only have a ranger to heal them.<br>
